# Testing — rsu_calc

## Test suite

| Command | What it runs |
|---|---|
| `npm test` | Vitest unit tests (52 tests — taxCalc, parseEtrade, surtaxFromSalePlan) |
| `npm run test:py` | Python regression tests (61 tests — tax_calc, parse_etrade fallback) |
| `npm run test:e2e` | Playwright E2E — smoke + demo-report full flow |

All commands run from the `app/` directory.

## Before every commit

Run unit tests before staging a commit:

```bash
cd app && npm test && npm run test:py
```

E2E tests are slower (require a build); run them when touching parsing, tax logic, or UI components.

## Bugfixes — always ask: is there a test?

When fixing a bug:
1. Check whether an existing test would have caught it — if so, update it.
2. If no test covers it, add one before or alongside the fix.
3. Preferred location:
   - Tax/math logic → `app/src/lib/__tests__/taxCalc.test.ts` or `surtaxFromSalePlan.test.ts`
   - Parser logic → `app/src/lib/__tests__/parseEtrade.test.ts` **and** `.cursor/skills/jfrog-equity-analyzer/test_tax_calc.py` (keep both in sync)
   - UI behaviour → `app/e2e/demo-report.spec.ts` or a new spec under `app/e2e/`

## New features and planning

When planning or implementing a new feature:
- Identify which test tier covers it (unit / E2E).
- Write or update tests as part of the same task — not as a follow-up.
- For new tax rules or bracket changes, mirror the test in both TypeScript and Python.
- For new UI sections, extend `demo-report.spec.ts` or add a dedicated E2E spec.

## CI

GitHub Actions runs all three suites on every PR and push to `dev`. Tests must pass before merging.
